section.section:
After the deduction of moneys under subsection (8), simulcast facility shall deduct a commission allowed under KRS 230.3615 with respect to all wagers made at the simulcast facility. The commission, less moneys allocated in subsection (8) of this section, shall be split as follows:
Thirty percent (30%) shall be allocated to the host track;
Forty-six and one-half percent (46.5%) to the purse program at the host track;
Thirteen and one-half percent (13.5%) to be retained by the track or tracks owning the simulcast facility for the purpose of application to expenses incurred in connection therewith;
Six percent (6%) to be allocated to the Kentucky Thoroughbred Owners and Breeders, Inc., to be expended as follows:
Up to three percent (3%) for capital improvements and promotion of off-track betting; and
The remainder for marketing and promoting the Kentucky Thoroughbred industry; and
Four percent (4%) to be allocated to the racing commission to be used for purses at county fairs in Kentucky licensed and approved by the racing commission, and for the standardbred sires stakes program established under KRS 230.770.
